      "score": 88,
      "action": "BUY",
      "entity": "THE BOEING COMPANY",
      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: THE BOEING COMPANY (BA)\n\n**ProPublica-Style Investigative Summary**\n\nBoeing has secured NASA contracts with a combined disclosed value exceeding **$32.9 billion**, representing one of the largest aerospace procurement concentrations awarded to a single contractor in recent federal contracting history. Boeing maintains active federal lobbying operations and has contributed to congressional campaigns of members sitting on the Senate Commerce Committee and House Science, Space, and Technology Committee, the legislative bodies with direct oversight jurisdiction over NASA appropriations. The company has previously faced documented federal scrutiny including a **2021 deferred prosecution agreement** with the DOJ related to 737 MAX certification fraud, a **$2.5 billion settlement**, and ongoing FAA regulatory investigations into manufacturing quality controls at its commercial division. Federal procurement records show Boeing has received **$154+ billion** in government contracts over the past decade, a pattern critics and government watchdogs including POGO *(Project on Government Oversight)* have repeatedly flagged as reflecting systemic revolving-door relationships between Boeing executives and federal regulatory and procurement agencies.\n\n---\n\n**⚠️ Signal Note:**\nThe $22.4B institutional accumulation signal, cross-referenced against 33 documented corruption indicators and active mega-contract awards, warrants continued monitoring of congressional disclosure filings and lobbying expenditure records.\n\n*Sources: USASpending.gov, DOJ, FAA, OpenSecrets, POGO*"
